cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper investigates QoS over wireless networks and the participation of various entities in providing QoS. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions mobile VoIP applications and their QoS requirements. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is mentioned in the paper as secure tunnels nullify QoS requests, so it is also a likely category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper touches on the role of routers and middleboxes in providing QoS and the impact of network neutrality on QoS.
